title.narrative: Assistance to Vulnerable Groups in the West Bank and Gaza

description.narrative: (West Bank and Gaza): The Assistance to Vulnerable Groups Project (AVG) implemented by the United Nations World Food Program (UNWFP) works to mitigate food vulnerability provides essential humanitarian relief. In 2016, the United Nations estimated that 22.5% of the population in the West Bank and Gaza were food insecure, a modest improvement in food security compared to 27% in 2014. .With FY 2017 funds, the AVG project will support continued provision of high-quality food assistance to help meet basic food needs and improve dietary diversity of 186,500 beneficiaries in the West Bank and Gaza, 95,000 of whom are in Gaza and 41,500 are in the West Bank. These beneficiaries will receive direct food support every three months. Funds will also be used to support 50,000 beneficiaries in the West Bank to use electronic voucher cards to purchase food at local food shops.

person-name.narrative: Anne Womer and Maryam Rashid, Desk Officers
